column14: SEE APPOVER NOTES BELLOW!!! Fair ADCP mmnt from d/s bridgeside.  Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ Stage is tracking well. Reset SE but did not reset OTT as it does not need it. MGH calc in field review. ADCP by Moving Boat  APPROVER REVIEW:  I TURNED OF SOME OF THE TOGGLED OFF TRANSECTS SO THAT WE HAD RECIPROCAL PAIRS.  THERE WAS 3 CONSEQUTIVE LEFT EDGE STARTS AND 3 Right EDGE STARTS., WHICH ARE NOT RECIPRICALS.      THEY ARE ALL IN THE BLACK ANYWAYS.    LEFT 000-002 OFF- FALSE STARTS.  LEFT 013 OFF - WAS A WEIRD OUTLIER. 014 WAS ITS RECIPRICAL SO LEFT IT OFF.  RE-RAN THRU QREV.   ONLY CHANGED IT FROM 1.592cms to 1.605cms., AND THE COV GOT SLIGHTLY WORSE FROM 4% to 5.7%, BUT DIDNT WANT TO REMOVE TRANSECTS UNNECCESARILY.     LOOP TEST WAS SHORT, BUT VALIDATED WITH SMB test.  NEAR MB VEL <0.012m/s SO NO MB APPLIED BY SYSTEM.  LOTS OF TRANSECTS COLLECTED SINCE ITS VERY NARROW.  RESULTED IN RELATIVELY LOW COV (5.7%).  EDGES WERE  ~19% OF TOTAL FLOW, BUT WERE CONSISTENT RESULTS EACH TIME.  COULD NOT GET CLOSER TO EDGE BECAUSE LOST BINS FROM SHALLOWING AND WEEDS.    4th beam was distrupted at times, so 3-beam solution was used by system.  likley from riparian plants.  FAIR MMNT GIVEN THE ENVIRONMENT.   MDF
